This paper deals with the study of equilibria in auction markets, which is a topic in game theory (cs.GT). The paper proposes a new solution concept called Restricted Envy-Free Pricing (REFP), which relaxes the envy-free and market-clearing conditions in Walrasian equilibrium. This involves computational aspects, which suggests that the paper could also belong to the categories of algorithms and data structures (cs.DS) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also discusses revenue-maximizing outcomes, which is a topic in computational economics (cs.EC) and machine learning (cs.LG).
